    "88372993": {
      "title": "Natural and induced sex ratio changes in populations of thelytokous Muscidifurax uniraptor (Hymenoptera; Pteromalidae)",
      "abstract": "Sex ratios in thelytokous Muscidifurax uniraptor Kogan and Legner from Puerto Rico were observed to change within a period of 3 months from predominantly female to predominantly male after 16 years in culture. Subsequently, the acquisition of new cultures from the field showed a similar change. Scheduling host presentation on alternate days skewed the sex ratio back toward females. The appearance of high numbers of males in thelytokous populations may signal an arrhenotokous cycle, as shown for one other species. The dynamics of M. uniraptor with its hosts in Puerto Rico may produce sex ratios closer to 50:50 during such a reproductive phase. The results prove the need to examine virgin females of newly acquired parasitic Hymenoptera cultures for thelytoky as phenotypically such cultures, judged by sex ratio alone, may appear arrhenotokous."
    }
  }
}